claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: Flow chart diagram of study population selection for vaccinated adults aged 18–64 in the 2018–2021 seasons, showing numbers of participants who received recombinant (Flublok) versus standard-dose vaccines and successive exclusions to arrive at final cohorts. does not support the claim because the figure only details participant inclusion/exclusion and vaccine type counts; it contains no data on antigenic match with WHO- or FDA-selected strains. Note: The figure is a participant flow diagram and does not address vaccine antigenic composition or matching.
